ce:section.ce:para:
To evaluate the effect of ions on sensor performance, the quenching experiments were carried out over H-ZIF-8/CDs@MIPs-2 with different ions (K+, Na+, Ca2+, Ba2+, Zn2+, Al3+, NH4
                        +, Mg2+, Pb2+, Cu2+, Ag+, Fe3+, Cd2+, Ni2+). These ions only displayed a weak fluorescence quenching effect, while noteworthy quenching effect was happened in the presence of BHb (Fig. 9
                        ). The results demonstrated that the H-ZIF-8/CDs@MIPs-2 sensor has the potential for the detection of BHb in complex environment. Generally, several metal ions can quench fluorescence intensity with CDs according to previous reports[43,44]. For this sensor, the printing player played a vital role to reduce the interference and increase the recognition effect to BHb.
